# NiceGUI Skills & Rules for EnterpriseŌĆæGrade UI (Based on core*.py)

This document defines the required skills, constraints, and rules for implementing
a stable, maintainable NiceGUI UI that replaces the Gradio UI layer.

---

## 1. Layout Rules

### 1.1 Use `ui.splitter` as the main shell
- Left panel: template sidebar (`splitter.before`)
- Right panel: tab workspace (`splitter.after`)
- Do NOT implement custom drag rails with raw JS.

### 1.2 Persist sidebar width

- Store width in `app.storage.user[pref_key('sidebar_width')]`.
- Restore width on page load.
- Requires `storage_secret` in `ui.run()`.

### 1.3 Avoid wrapping NiceGUI components inside raw HTML
- HTML is allowed only for small fragments (titles, tables).
- All interactive components must be NiceGUI elements.

---

## 2. State Management Rules

### 2.0 Default principal: `admin`

- Default account is always `user:admin`. No login UI while `known_usernames()` is only `['admin']`.
- When additional users are added, `login_required()` becomes true; show login and set `app.storage.user['username']`.
- All handlers resolve state via `SessionRegistry.for_current()`; never read unpartitioned module globals.
- Future permission limits apply per user (e.g. shrink `admin` grants), not by bypassing `principal_id` or sharing one global `SessionState`.

### 2.1 Every principal must have an isolated `SessionState`

- Use `SessionRegistry.for_current()` keyed by `principal_id` (`user:admin`, `user:{name}`, ŌĆ”).
- A module-level `SessionRegistry: dict[str, SessionState]` is allowed; a single shared `SessionState` is not.
- Store runtime objects (cfg, db, writer, draft, session_rows) inside that principal's `SessionState`.
- Single-user mode: all visitors use `user:admin` and share one workspace session (no login).

### 2.2 Use `@ui.refreshable` for dynamic UI
- Dynamic input fields
- Dynamic tables
- Dynamic TOML report
- Dynamic status labels

### 2.3 Use `app.storage.user` for persistent UI preferences

- Use `pref_key(name)` from `nicegui_ui.components.auth` (e.g. `user:admin:sidebar_width`).
- Sidebar width, collapsed state, last selected DB suffix.
- Requires `storage_secret` in `ui.run()`.

